{"block_id": "B062", "document_id": "0001193125-14-455030", "ordinal": 62, "start_line": 1523, "end_line": 1524, "raw_text": "On September 29, 2014, Party F communicated to Deutsche Bank that a combination with Penford\nwas not a suitable strategic fit and declined to pursue further discussions regarding a transaction.", "clean_text": "On September 29, 2014, Party F communicated to Deutsche Bank that a combination with Penford was not a suitable strategic fit and declined to pursue further discussions regarding a transaction.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "September 29, 2014", "normalized": "2014-09-29", "precision": "exact_day"}], "entity_mentions": [{"raw_text": "Party F", "entity_type": "party_alias"}], "evidence_density": 2, "temporal_phase": "bidding"}
{"block_id": "B063", "document_id": "0001193125-14-455030", "ordinal": 63, "start_line": 1526, "end_line": 1530, "raw_text": "Also on September 29, 2014, the\nboard met with members of management and representatives of Perkins Coie and Deutsche Bank. Deutsche Bank reviewed with the board a current status report on the market check process, including the recent management presentation provided to Party C\nand its discussions with Party F. Deutsche Bank also updated the board on the status of ongoing due diligence. The board discussed the current proposal from Ingredion, and Mr. Malkoski observed that the proposed price of $18.25 or $18.50 per\nshare represented a significant increase from Ingredion\u0092s initial indication of $16.00 (based on the 52-week high). However, the board indicated it would prefer to see the per share price increase by an additional $0.50 to $1.00 in order to\nincrease the value ultimately to be received by Penford\u0092s shareholders. The board approved moving forward with further negotiations with Ingredion.", "clean_text": "Also on September 29, 2014, the board met with members of management and representatives of Perkins Coie and Deutsche Bank. Deutsche Bank reviewed with the board a current status report on the market check process, including the recent management presentation provided to Party C and its discussions with Party F. Deutsche Bank also updated the board on the status of ongoing due diligence. The board discussed the current proposal from Ingredion, and Mr. Malkoski observed that the proposed price of $18.25 or $18.50 per share represented a significant increase from Ingredion\u0092s initial indication of $16.00 (based on the 52-week high). However, the board indicated it would prefer to see the per share price increase by an additional $0.50 to $1.00 in order to increase the value ultimately to be received by Penford\u0092s shareholders. The board approved moving forward with further negotiations with Ingredion.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "September 29, 2014", "normalized": "2014-09-29", "precision": "exact_day"}], "entity_mentions": [{"raw_text": "Party C", "entity_type": "party_alias"}, {"raw_text": "Party F", "entity_type": "party_alias"}, {"raw_text": "the board", "entity_type": "party_alias"}], "evidence_density": 4, "temporal_phase": "bidding"}
{"block_id": "B064", "document_id": "0001193125-14-455030", "ordinal": 64, "start_line": 1532, "end_line": 1535, "raw_text": "On September 30, 2014, Penford and Party A executed a nondisclosure and standstill agreement, which included standard confidentiality\nrestrictions and a standstill provision that automatically expired upon the public announcement of the entering into a definitive agreement for a sale of 50% or more of the capital stock of Penford, and Deutsche Bank provided Party A with\ninformation regarding Penford\u0092s operations, business segments, product applications and technologies, end markets, key leadership, supply chain and manufacturing facilities, historical financial performance and financial projections. Deutsche\nBank informed Party A that Penford would not provide in-person management presentations unless there was an indication that Party A\u0092s proposed offer price would be competitive, which Deutsche Bank advised would likely be over $20.00 per share.", "clean_text": "On September 30, 2014, Penford and Party A executed a nondisclosure and standstill agreement, which included standard confidentiality restrictions and a standstill provision that automatically expired upon the public announcement of the entering into a definitive agreement for a sale of 50% or more of the capital stock of Penford, and Deutsche Bank provided Party A with information regarding Penford\u0092s operations, business segments, product applications and technologies, end markets, key leadership, supply chain and manufacturing facilities, historical financial performance and financial projections. Deutsche Bank informed Party A that Penford would not provide in-person management presentations unless there was an indication that Party A\u0092s proposed offer price would be competitive, which Deutsche Bank advised would likely be over $20.00 per share.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "September 30, 2014", "normalized": "2014-09-30", "precision": "exact_day"}], "entity_mentions": [{"raw_text": "Party A", "entity_type": "party_alias"}], "evidence_density": 5, "temporal_phase": "outcome"}
{"block_id": "B065", "document_id": "0001193125-14-455030", "ordinal": 65, "start_line": 1537, "end_line": 1540, "raw_text": "On October 1, 2014, Deutsche Bank contacted J. P. Morgan Securities to provide feedback on the potential price increase discussed on\nSeptember 17, 2014, advising J. P. Morgan Securities that Penford\u0092s board of directors was disappointed with the $18.25 to $18.50 proposal, and that, based on Deutsche Bank\u0092s discussions with Penford\u0092s board of directors, Penford\nexpected a higher value based on the additional information regarding Penford that had been provided to Ingredion as part of the due diligence process. Deutsche Bank further explained that Penford\u0092s board of directors had wanted a purchase\nprice of at least $20.00 per share.", "clean_text": "On October 1, 2014, Deutsche Bank contacted J. P. Morgan Securities to provide feedback on the potential price increase discussed on September 17, 2014, advising J. P. Morgan Securities that Penford\u0092s board of directors was disappointed with the $18.25 to $18.50 proposal, and that, based on Deutsche Bank\u0092s discussions with Penford\u0092s board of directors, Penford expected a higher value based on the additional information regarding Penford that had been provided to Ingredion as part of the due diligence process. Deutsche Bank further explained that Penford\u0092s board of directors had wanted a purchase price of at least $20.00 per share.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "October 1, 2014", "normalized": "2014-10-01", "precision": "exact_day"}, {"raw_text": "September 17, 2014", "normalized": "2014-09-17", "precision": "exact_day"}], "entity_mentions": [], "evidence_density": 4, "temporal_phase": "bidding"}
{"block_id": "B066", "document_id": "0001193125-14-455030", "ordinal": 66, "start_line": 1542, "end_line": 1548, "raw_text": "On October 2, 2014, Mr. Malkoski and Mr. Fortnum had a call to discuss the\nOctober 1 discussion between Deutsche Bank and J. P. Morgan Securities. Mr. Fortnum asked Mr. Malkoski to confirm whether Penford\u0092s board was unwilling to move forward with a transaction unless Ingredion was able to offer a price\nin the $20.00 per share range. Mr. Malkoski clarified that the board wanted that offer price, but was willing to proceed with negotiations. However, Mr. Malkoski then stated that because Ingredion\u0092s proposal was below that preferred\nprice, Penford felt it necessary to provide more information and schedule additional meetings in order to provide Ingredion with the support it needed to increase the offer price. Mr. Malkoski noted that the impact of this would be to delay a\npotential signing of a definitive agreement beyond Ingredion\u0092s preferred timing for announcement of a transaction. Mr. Fortnum stated that Ingredion was still struggling to justify the valuation for a transaction at a higher price.\nMr. Fortnum then stated that Ingredion was prepared to move forward based on a proposed price of $18.50 per share on a fully diluted basis. Mr. Malkoski responded that that price was unlikely to be high enough for Penford\u0092s board of\ndirectors to recommend the transaction to shareholders.", "clean_text": "On October 2, 2014, Mr. Malkoski and Mr. Fortnum had a call to discuss the October 1 discussion between Deutsche Bank and J. P. Morgan Securities. Mr. Fortnum asked Mr. Malkoski to confirm whether Penford\u0092s board was unwilling to move forward with a transaction unless Ingredion was able to offer a price in the $20.00 per share range. Mr. Malkoski clarified that the board wanted that offer price, but was willing to proceed with negotiations. However, Mr. Malkoski then stated that because Ingredion\u0092s proposal was below that preferred price, Penford felt it necessary to provide more information and schedule additional meetings in order to provide Ingredion with the support it needed to increase the offer price. Mr. Malkoski noted that the impact of this would be to delay a potential signing of a definitive agreement beyond Ingredion\u0092s preferred timing for announcement of a transaction. Mr. Fortnum stated that Ingredion was still struggling to justify the valuation for a transaction at a higher price. Mr. Fortnum then stated that Ingredion was prepared to move forward based on a proposed price of $18.50 per share on a fully diluted basis. Mr. Malkoski responded that that price was unlikely to be high enough for Penford\u0092s board of directors to recommend the transaction to shareholders.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "October 2, 2014", "normalized": "2014-10-02", "precision": "exact_day"}, {"raw_text": "October", "normalized": null, "precision": "unknown"}], "entity_mentions": [{"raw_text": "the board", "entity_type": "party_alias"}], "evidence_density": 3, "temporal_phase": "bidding"}
{"block_id": "B067", "document_id": "0001193125-14-455030", "ordinal": 67, "start_line": 1550, "end_line": 1552, "raw_text": "On October 2, 2014, Penford received a letter from Ingredion regarding\nits indication of interest and increasing the proposed price to $19.00 per share of outstanding Penford capital stock on a fully diluted basis. Based on the $12.77 per share closing price of Penford\u0092s common stock on October 1, 2014, the\nlast business day prior to receiving this revised indication of interest, the proposed price of $19.00 represented a 49% premium.", "clean_text": "On October 2, 2014, Penford received a letter from Ingredion regarding its indication of interest and increasing the proposed price to $19.00 per share of outstanding Penford capital stock on a fully diluted basis. Based on the $12.77 per share closing price of Penford\u0092s common stock on October 1, 2014, the last business day prior to receiving this revised indication of interest, the proposed price of $19.00 represented a 49% premium.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "October 2, 2014", "normalized": "2014-10-02", "precision": "exact_day"}, {"raw_text": "October 1, 2014", "normalized": "2014-10-01", "precision": "exact_day"}], "entity_mentions": [], "evidence_density": 3, "temporal_phase": "outcome"}
{"block_id": "B068", "document_id": "0001193125-14-455030", "ordinal": 68, "start_line": 1554, "end_line": 1558, "raw_text": "On October 3, 2014, the board met with members of management and representatives of Perkins Coie and representatives of Deutsche Bank.\nDeutsche Bank reviewed with the board recent developments, including reviewing in detail the revised indication of interest from Ingredion increasing the proposed price per share of the Company\u0092s stock on a fully diluted basis to $19.00 per\nshare. Deutsche Bank also provided the board with an update on the status of the market check process, stating that based on transaction size and market conditions, it was unlikely Party A would submit any indication of interest that would reflect\nthe requested price of $20.00 per share. Deutsche Bank also updated the board that no other companies that had been contacted during the market check process indicated they would provide a proposal or other indication of interest. The board\ndiscussed the", "clean_text": "On October 3, 2014, the board met with members of management and representatives of Perkins Coie and representatives of Deutsche Bank. Deutsche Bank reviewed with the board recent developments, including reviewing in detail the revised indication of interest from Ingredion increasing the proposed price per share of the Company\u0092s stock on a fully diluted basis to $19.00 per share. Deutsche Bank also provided the board with an update on the status of the market check process, stating that based on transaction size and market conditions, it was unlikely Party A would submit any indication of interest that would reflect the requested price of $20.00 per share. Deutsche Bank also updated the board that no other companies that had been contacted during the market check process indicated they would provide a proposal or other indication of interest. The board discussed the", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "October 3, 2014", "normalized": "2014-10-03", "precision": "exact_day"}], "entity_mentions": [{"raw_text": "INGREDION INC", "entity_type": "acquirer"}, {"raw_text": "Party A", "entity_type": "party_alias"}, {"raw_text": "the Company", "entity_type": "party_alias"}, {"raw_text": "the board", "entity_type": "party_alias"}], "evidence_density": 3, "temporal_phase": "bidding"}
{"block_id": "B069", "document_id": "0001193125-14-455030", "ordinal": 69, "start_line": 1560, "end_line": 1560, "raw_text": "30", "clean_text": "30", "is_heading": true, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [], "entity_mentions": [], "evidence_density": 0, "temporal_phase": "other"}
{"block_id": "B070", "document_id": "0001193125-14-455030", "ordinal": 70, "start_line": 1563, "end_line": 1564, "raw_text": "status of negotiations and the market check process, including whether Party G should be contacted given the status of the negotiations and the market check. After further discussion, with input\nfrom Deutsche Bank, the directors present at the board meeting unanimously directed management to proceed to negotiate and finalize a definitive agreement with Ingredion.", "clean_text": "status of negotiations and the market check process, including whether Party G should be contacted given the status of the negotiations and the market check. After further discussion, with input from Deutsche Bank, the directors present at the board meeting unanimously directed management to proceed to negotiate and finalize a definitive agreement with Ingredion.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [], "entity_mentions": [{"raw_text": "Party G", "entity_type": "party_alias"}, {"raw_text": "the board", "entity_type": "party_alias"}], "evidence_density": 1, "temporal_phase": "initiation"}
{"block_id": "B071", "document_id": "0001193125-14-455030", "ordinal": 71, "start_line": 1566, "end_line": 1567, "raw_text": "Later on October 3, 2014, Mr. Malkoski informed Mr. Fortnum that the Penford board had authorized management to move forward\nwith negotiating the draft merger agreement. Mr. Malkoski and Mr. Fortnum agreed that their teams should meet in person in Chicago the following week to review and negotiate the draft merger agreement.", "clean_text": "Later on October 3, 2014, Mr. Malkoski informed Mr. Fortnum that the Penford board had authorized management to move forward with negotiating the draft merger agreement. Mr. Malkoski and Mr. Fortnum agreed that their teams should meet in person in Chicago the following week to review and negotiate the draft merger agreement.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "October 3, 2014", "normalized": "2014-10-03", "precision": "exact_day"}], "entity_mentions": [], "evidence_density": 3, "temporal_phase": "outcome"}
{"block_id": "B072", "document_id": "0001193125-14-455030", "ordinal": 72, "start_line": 1569, "end_line": 1571, "raw_text": "Later on October 3, 2014, Perkins Coie sent a revised draft of the merger agreement to Sidley Austin LLP (referred to as Sidley Austin),\nIngredion\u0092s legal counsel. On October 4, Deutsche Bank followed up with Party A regarding the potential transaction with Penford, pursuant to which Party A indicated any offer would be below $17.50 - $18.00 per share in cash. Deutsche Bank\nencouraged Party A to submit a letter of interest that could be reviewed by the board of directors.", "clean_text": "Later on October 3, 2014, Perkins Coie sent a revised draft of the merger agreement to Sidley Austin LLP (referred to as Sidley Austin), Ingredion\u0092s legal counsel. On October 4, Deutsche Bank followed up with Party A regarding the potential transaction with Penford, pursuant to which Party A indicated any offer would be below $17.50 - $18.00 per share in cash. Deutsche Bank encouraged Party A to submit a letter of interest that could be reviewed by the board of directors.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "October 3, 2014", "normalized": "2014-10-03", "precision": "exact_day"}, {"raw_text": "October", "normalized": null, "precision": "unknown"}], "entity_mentions": [{"raw_text": "Party A", "entity_type": "party_alias"}, {"raw_text": "the board", "entity_type": "party_alias"}], "evidence_density": 4, "temporal_phase": "outcome"}
{"block_id": "B073", "document_id": "0001193125-14-455030", "ordinal": 73, "start_line": 1573, "end_line": 1576, "raw_text": "On October 6, 2014, Perkins Coie\nand Sidley Austin discussed the draft merger agreement and certain open issues, including, but not limited to, the requirement for significant shareholders to enter into voting and support agreements, the finalization of fiscal 2014 financial\nstatements and delivery thereof as a closing condition, the scope of certain representations and warranties of the Company, the scope of the restrictions on the operations of Penford prior to closing, the non-solicitation obligations of the Company\nwith respect to acquisition proposals, the circumstances under which a termination fee would be payable by the Company and the requirement to divest or otherwise agree to any business restrictions in the context of antitrust approvals.", "clean_text": "On October 6, 2014, Perkins Coie and Sidley Austin discussed the draft merger agreement and certain open issues, including, but not limited to, the requirement for significant shareholders to enter into voting and support agreements, the finalization of fiscal 2014 financial statements and delivery thereof as a closing condition, the scope of certain representations and warranties of the Company, the scope of the restrictions on the operations of Penford prior to closing, the non-solicitation obligations of the Company with respect to acquisition proposals, the circumstances under which a termination fee would be payable by the Company and the requirement to divest or otherwise agree to any business restrictions in the context of antitrust approvals.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "October 6, 2014", "normalized": "2014-10-06", "precision": "exact_day"}], "entity_mentions": [{"raw_text": "the Company", "entity_type": "party_alias"}], "evidence_density": 4, "temporal_phase": "outcome"}
{"block_id": "B074", "document_id": "0001193125-14-455030", "ordinal": 74, "start_line": 1578, "end_line": 1580, "raw_text": "On October 7, 2014, Perkins Coie contacted Milbank, Tweed, Hadley & McCloy, LLP (referred to as Milbank), legal counsel to\nSEACOR, regarding Ingredion\u0092s request for SEACOR to enter into a voting and support agreement, during which conversation, Milbank indicated that conceptually, a voting and support agreement to support the transaction would be acceptable,\nsubject to discussions with SEACOR, provided that the voting and support agreement terminated in the event the executed merger agreement would be terminated in the event of a superior offer.", "clean_text": "On October 7, 2014, Perkins Coie contacted Milbank, Tweed, Hadley & McCloy, LLP (referred to as Milbank), legal counsel to SEACOR, regarding Ingredion\u0092s request for SEACOR to enter into a voting and support agreement, during which conversation, Milbank indicated that conceptually, a voting and support agreement to support the transaction would be acceptable, subject to discussions with SEACOR, provided that the voting and support agreement terminated in the event the executed merger agreement would be terminated in the event of a superior offer.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "October 7, 2014", "normalized": "2014-10-07", "precision": "exact_day"}], "entity_mentions": [], "evidence_density": 3, "temporal_phase": "outcome"}
{"block_id": "B075", "document_id": "0001193125-14-455030", "ordinal": 75, "start_line": 1582, "end_line": 1582, "raw_text": "On October 8, 2014, Sidley Austin circulated a revised draft of the merger agreement to Perkins Coie.", "clean_text": "On October 8, 2014, Sidley Austin circulated a revised draft of the merger agreement to Perkins Coie.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "October 8, 2014", "normalized": "2014-10-08", "precision": "exact_day"}], "entity_mentions": [], "evidence_density": 1, "temporal_phase": "outcome"}
{"block_id": "B076", "document_id": "0001193125-14-455030", "ordinal": 76, "start_line": 1584, "end_line": 1585, "raw_text": "Also on October 8, 2014, Deutsche Bank met with representatives from Party D, who indicated that it did not intend to move forward with\ndiscussions regarding a potential transaction involving the Company.", "clean_text": "Also on October 8, 2014, Deutsche Bank met with representatives from Party D, who indicated that it did not intend to move forward with discussions regarding a potential transaction involving the Company.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "October 8, 2014", "normalized": "2014-10-08", "precision": "exact_day"}], "entity_mentions": [{"raw_text": "Party D", "entity_type": "party_alias"}, {"raw_text": "the Company", "entity_type": "party_alias"}], "evidence_density": 2, "temporal_phase": "bidding"}
{"block_id": "B077", "document_id": "0001193125-14-455030", "ordinal": 77, "start_line": 1587, "end_line": 1591, "raw_text": "On October 9, 2014, certain members of management of each of\nPenford and Ingredion, and representatives of their legal advisors, Perkins Coie and Sidley Austin, respectively, and their financial advisors, Deutsche Bank and J. P. Morgan Securities, respectively, met in person in Chicago at the offices of Sidley\nAustin to assist in reviewing and negotiating remaining open issues in the draft merger agreement, including with respect to the delivery of fiscal 2014 financial statements as a closing condition, the scope of certain representations and warranties\nof the Company, the scope of the restrictions on the operations of Penford prior to the closing of the merger agreement, the non-solicitation obligations of the Company with respect to acquisition proposals, the circumstances under which a\ntermination fee would be payable by the Company and the requirement to divest or otherwise agree to any business restrictions in the context of antitrust approvals.", "clean_text": "On October 9, 2014, certain members of management of each of Penford and Ingredion, and representatives of their legal advisors, Perkins Coie and Sidley Austin, respectively, and their financial advisors, Deutsche Bank and J. P. Morgan Securities, respectively, met in person in Chicago at the offices of Sidley Austin to assist in reviewing and negotiating remaining open issues in the draft merger agreement, including with respect to the delivery of fiscal 2014 financial statements as a closing condition, the scope of certain representations and warranties of the Company, the scope of the restrictions on the operations of Penford prior to the closing of the merger agreement, the non-solicitation obligations of the Company with respect to acquisition proposals, the circumstances under which a termination fee would be payable by the Company and the requirement to divest or otherwise agree to any business restrictions in the context of antitrust approvals.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "October 9, 2014", "normalized": "2014-10-09", "precision": "exact_day"}], "entity_mentions": [{"raw_text": "the Company", "entity_type": "party_alias"}], "evidence_density": 4, "temporal_phase": "outcome"}
{"block_id": "B078", "document_id": "0001193125-14-455030", "ordinal": 78, "start_line": 1593, "end_line": 1595, "raw_text": "On October 10, 2014, Sidley Austin provided an updated draft of the merger agreement to Perkins Coie, and on October 11, 2014,\nPerkins Coie sent a revised draft of the merger agreement to Sidley Austin. Also, on October 10, 2014, Sidley Austin distributed an initial draft of the voting and support agreement to be entered into with SEACOR. Later on October 11,\n2014, Perkins Coie sent an initial draft of the disclosure letter to Sidley Austin, followed by a revised version on October 12, 2014.", "clean_text": "On October 10, 2014, Sidley Austin provided an updated draft of the merger agreement to Perkins Coie, and on October 11, 2014, Perkins Coie sent a revised draft of the merger agreement to Sidley Austin. Also, on October 10, 2014, Sidley Austin distributed an initial draft of the voting and support agreement to be entered into with SEACOR. Later on October 11, 2014, Perkins Coie sent an initial draft of the disclosure letter to Sidley Austin, followed by a revised version on October 12, 2014.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "October 10, 2014", "normalized": "2014-10-10", "precision": "exact_day"}, {"raw_text": "October 11, 2014", "normalized": "2014-10-11", "precision": "exact_day"}, {"raw_text": "October 12, 2014", "normalized": "2014-10-12", "precision": "exact_day"}], "entity_mentions": [], "evidence_density": 2, "temporal_phase": "outcome"}
{"block_id": "B079", "document_id": "0001193125-14-455030", "ordinal": 79, "start_line": 1597, "end_line": 1598, "raw_text": "On October 11, 2014, Penford provided Ingredion with draft financial statements for the fiscal year ended August 31, 2014 (referred\nto as the 2014 draft financial statements), which reflected lower volume, lower revenue", "clean_text": "On October 11, 2014, Penford provided Ingredion with draft financial statements for the fiscal year ended August 31, 2014 (referred to as the 2014 draft financial statements), which reflected lower volume, lower revenue", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "October 11, 2014", "normalized": "2014-10-11", "precision": "exact_day"}, {"raw_text": "August 31, 2014", "normalized": "2014-08-31", "precision": "exact_day"}], "entity_mentions": [], "evidence_density": 0, "temporal_phase": "other"}
